---
title: Apricot Balsamic Glazed Bavette Steak with Ginger Garlic Rice & Sesame Green Beans
description: A glaze you’ll be thinking about for days! Apricot jam meets balsamic vinegar for a sweet, sticky, and tangy sauce on savory pork filets. Don’t sleep on the sides because they get lots of flavor love, too: jasmine rice cooked with ginger, garlic, and stock, plus steamed green beans that get a nutty aroma from sesame oil. Drizzle everything with soy sauce for serious umami satisfaction.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/686e00a4249cc147aea828fb-2ab7e386.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/686e00a4249cc147aea828fb-en-US.pdf
cuisine: North America
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/apricot-balsamic-glazed-bavette-steak-686e00a4249cc147aea828fb
servings: 2
time required: 45 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 980 kcal
  fat: 49 g
  saturated fat: 19 g
  carbohydrates: 90 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1460 mg
---

Wash and dry produce (except green beans).

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Halve, peel, and mince half the @shallot{1}.

== Ginger Garlic Rice ==

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a small #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add ginger, scallion whites, and half the garlic; cook until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1/2} and @water{1 1/4%cups}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Steak ==

Pat @bavette steak{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @fry seasoning{1%tsp}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook, turning occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wash out pan.

== Apricot Balsamic Glaze ==

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add minced shallot and cook until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @apricot jam{1} and @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp}; simmer until syrupy, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @water{1/4%cup}, remaining @chicken stock concentrate{1/2}, and @sugar{1%tsp}. Bring to a boil, then lower heat; simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Sesame Green Beans ==

Pierce green bean bag with a #fork{}; place bag on a #plate{}. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> No microwave? No problem! Steam beans in a small pot with a splash of water until just tender, 5-7 minutes.

Carefully transfer @green beans{6%oz} to a #medium bowl{}. Toss with @sesame oil{1%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a fork; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir any resting juices from pork into pan with glaze.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide rice, pork, and green beans between plates. Drizzle pork with glaze. Top everything with scallion greens and @soy sauce{2%tbsp} to taste. Serve.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.